# Overview

## Mandatory Behavior

- Every LLM call must define a schema.
- Reject output if:
  - Any field is missing.
  - Any extra field exists.
  - Types do not match.
- Empty values must be explicit.
  - Use "" for strings.
  - Use [] for arrays.
  - Use null only if allowed.

## Example Schema Pattern

{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "title": "",
    "summary": "",
    "items": []
  },
  "error": null
}

## Validation Rules

- success is boolean.
- data is null when success is false.
- error is null when success is true.
- Never mix data and error.

## n8n Enforcement Pattern

- LLM node returns JSON.
- IF node checks:
  - success === true
- Code node validates:
  - Object keys
  - Array types
  - String types
- Fail fast on mismatch.

## Failure Output Schema

{
  "success": false,
  "data": null,
  "error": {
    "code": "",
    "message": ""
  }
}

## Forbidden

- Partial objects.
- Implicit defaults.
- Human-readable errors.
